Parent: PL‑1105 / PL‑1106 CSYS: PL_Fill_CS / PL_Rinse_CS (panel origins at port centers)
Datums: A=panel face • B=lower edge • C=LH edge

A. Mechanical / Panel Features
Feature	Requirement
Fill port	1.5″ cam‑lock female dry‑break; panel cut‑out per vendor; 6× M6 on Ø76 mm B.C.; gasket groove 3×3 mm
Rinse return	0.5″ cam‑lock; 4× M5 on Ø45 mm B.C.
Panel plate	5052‑H32 t=2.5 mm; edge hem optional; drain notch; labels “FILL/RINSE” laser‑etch
Grounding	M6 ground lug within 50 mm; bond <2.5 mΩ
B. Performance / Fluids

Fill rate: ≥227 L/min [≥60 gpm]; Rinse: 38–76 L/min [10–20 gpm].

Chem compatibility: wetted materials Viton/PTFE/SS316.

Purge: line purge ≤90 s at rinse flow.

C. Parameter Bindings

spray.fill_BC_D_mm, spray.rinse_BC_D_mm, spray.flow_fill_gpm, spray.flow_rinse_gpm

D. Deliverables

CAD + STEP; panel drawings; pressure/leak test; flow bench card.

E. Acceptance Tests

Hydrostatic: 1.25× working pressure, 5 min, no leaks.

Flow: achieve ≥60 gpm fill to test tank @ specified head; rinse ≥10 gpm.

Purge: ≤90 s to clean water at outlet.

Assumptions & Notes: Quick‑disconnect couplers to be keyed; color‑coded caps recommended.
